JavaScript Basics Introduction JavaScript is a programming language that enables interactive web pages. It is an essential part of web applications, and nearly all modern websites use it.
Variables In JavaScript, you can declare variables using var, let, or const:
// Using var (older way) var name = &#34;John&#34;; // Using let (modern way, block-scoped) let age = 30; // Using const (for values that won&#39;t change) const PI = 3.
